The Cogeneration Association of California and EPUC have jointly filed an =
=20
application?for relief at the CPUC.? The filing states that the CPUC,  alon=
g=20
with the EOB, has the affirmative responsibility to undertake an =20
investigation into specific practices of ISO:
?
"The Commission and the EOB are to determine if any policy or action =20
undertaken by the ISO, directly or indirectly, unreasonably discourages the=
 =20
retention of existing self-generation or cogeneration, or the connection of=
=20
new  self-generation or cogeneration resources to meet California=01,s need=
 for=20
electric  power.? If the investigation results in an affirmative finding,=
=20
then the  Commission and the EOB must undertake all necessary efforts to=20
revise, mitigate,  or eliminate offending policy or action of the ISO.This=
=20
application  affirmatively demonstrates the offending policies and actions=
=20
undertaken by the  ISO in violation of Section 372(f), and seeks remedial=
=20
actions for these  unreasonable policies and actions."
?
A copy of the application is attached for your information.
